TRIGGER: Client-side automation (not a server command)

Syntax: (configure in your MUD client)

DESCRIPTION:
  Triggers are handled by your MUD client, not by the AetherMUD server.
  A trigger watches incoming text and runs client actions (send a
  command, highlight text, play a sound, etc.).

  Examples in Mudlet:
    - create a trigger on "You are hungry" to auto-eat food
    - highlight your name in room text

  The server has no trigger editor. Configure triggers in Mudlet,
  MUSHclient, or whichever client you use.

  The related help topic "triggers" covers the same subject.

SEE ALSO: lineecho, alias, prompt
